<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="59" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 23700/14.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Beaupré</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-12"><hi rend="italic">April 12,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to legation’s, April 11, relative to extradition of Knepper,
                            Mr. Hale says permission for transit has not been obtained and instructs
                            Mr. Beaupré to cooperate with the legation at Brussels to secure same,
                            as agent is sailing on this date.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>